---
source: src/graph/mod.rs
assertion: graph refresh rebuilds derived projection from FrankenSQLite source truth
schema:
  report: ee.graph.centrality_refresh.v1
  snapshot: ee.graph.refresh_snapshot.v1
contracts:
  - refresh reads memory_links from FrankenSQLite as source of truth
  - derived graph snapshot is persisted with version and source_generation
  - snapshot content_hash is deterministic given same memory links
  - dry-run reports what would be done without mutating snapshots
  - stale or missing snapshot returns degraded status with repair hint
  - min_weight and min_confidence options filter links before projection
  - link_limit caps the maximum links processed for large graphs
  - timing breakdown includes projection_ms, pagerank_ms, betweenness_ms
  - concurrent writers are serialized via advisory lock
  - lock contention returns SnapshotLockHeld error with holder info
  - JSON stdout includes workspace_id and optional snapshot metadata
  - GraphFeatureDisabled status when graph feature is not compiled in
evidence:
  - CentralityRefreshOptions.dry_run
  - CentralityRefreshOptions.min_weight
  - CentralityRefreshOptions.min_confidence
  - CentralityRefreshOptions.link_limit
  - GraphRefreshSnapshot.snapshot_version
  - GraphRefreshSnapshot.source_generation
  - GraphRefreshSnapshot.content_hash
  - GraphRefreshJobReport.workspace_id
  - CentralityRefreshStatus
